cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.NI 

This paper discusses the adoption patterns of Let's Encrypt, a new development in the security landscape, and analyzes data from Certificate Transparency Logs, Censys, Alexa's historic records, Geolocation databases, and VirusTotal. The paper focuses on the impact of Let's Encrypt on HTTPS adoption and server misconfigurations, which are relevant to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), cybercrime (cs.CY), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
